(175352, 'DA7482AE-BDA6-4BCE-9D33-E2B963162EF1', 'btw, I’m finding it a really interesting experience to take in you comments about what pulls you to me. sweetness, empathy, etc. Most people describe me as a bull dog/aggressive, passionate, relentless. I don’t think people think I’m not sweet, but it wouldn’t be the first way people would describe me. So kinda getting used to that from you. ', '460328098000000000', '460328154000000000', 0, 'Nitzan', 'David', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'None', 'nitzan.pelman@gmail.com', '2015-08-03T13:54:58'),
(175533, 'DBE4A542-3CCA-4E5E-9EEC-0670E6E85D36', 'I see evidence of these qualities too, and like many aspects of each of our personalities we can describe them from the positive manifestation or the negative. When we are in honeymoon period, sure we will accentuate the positive...maybe exaggerate on some accounts....and not see the negative. But it will come out and we will Piss each other off and hurt one other...then what? The trick is in the dynamic, right? Learning how to negotiate these differences and be strengthened by them. You may be relentless and while im ambitious, by nature I''m not aggressive. So, it is helpful to recognize this and be aware of situations when this could cause conflict (or worse, avoid conflict that then builds up). Awareness is key. Communication is key. Love and respect, compromise...all that stuff.  I believe it is worth it.  Much longer conversation for sure. But on to ikea!', '460331233000000000', '460331423000000000', 1, 'David', 'Nitzan', 0, '', '', '', 'iMessage', 'None', 'David', '2015-08-03T14:47:13'),
